OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782047474
OL,3,CTartan Army fans still keeping World
OL,4,CCup dream alive despite Morocco defeat
OL,6,FAt the Boston Stadium in Foxborough
OL,7,Fahead of kick-off, Tartan Army fans
OL,8,Fwere eating, drinking and generally
OL,9,Fhaving a lot of fun.
OL,11,FLots of supporters in kilts mingled
OL,12,Famong groups of Morocco fans draped in
OL,13,Ftheir nation's colours and flag.
OL,15,FThe atmosphere was full of excitement
OL,16,Fand anticipation as cheers and chants
OL,17,Fcaught and spread throughout the
OL,18,Fcrowds.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782047474
OL,3,CTartan Army fans still keeping World
OL,4,CCup dream alive despite Morocco defeat
OL,6,FAmid all the revelry and passion,
OL,7,Fthere was a moment of poignancy during
OL,8,Fthe game as the crowd inside the
OL,9,Fstadium applauded in unison in the
OL,10,F76th minute in tribute to Donny
OL,11,FStrathie, the Scotland fan who died in
OL,12,FBoston on Sunday before he had the
OL,13,Fchance to fulfil a dream of watching
OL,14,Fhis team play in the World Cup.
OL,16,FIn downtown Boston, bars were packed
OL,17,Fwith Scotland fans who journeyed to
OL,18,Fthe US city to soak up the atmosphere
OL,19,Fdespite not having tickets for the
OL,20,Fgame.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782047474
OL,3,CTartan Army fans still keeping World
OL,4,CCup dream alive despite Morocco defeat
OL,6,FMorocco's early goal failed to dampen
OL,7,Fspirts inside Hennessy's Bar.
OL,9,FTartan Army fans continued to cheer
OL,10,Ffor their team throughout.
OL,12,FScott McNab, 34, from Edinburgh, said
OL,13,Fhe felt Scotland were "far too
OL,14,Fdefensive" in the first half.
OL,16,F"We sat in and played for the draw,
OL,17,Fand then second half came out, made
OL,18,Fchanges, (Ben) Gannon-Doak made a
OL,19,Fmassive difference and I feel like in
OL,20,Fthe second half they (Morocco) were
OL,21,Fclinging on," he said.
OL,26,@uD@WOUvD@JO]xD@AOU}D@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782047474
OL,3,CTartan Army fans still keeping World
OL,4,CCup dream alive despite Morocco defeat
OL,6,F"In my opinion, we've been robbed of
OL,7,Fat least one penalty to eventually get
OL,8,Fa point. But I don't want to be
OL,9,Fnegative. We lost by one. Goal
OL,10,Fdifference is what it's going to come
OL,11,Fdown to.
OL,13,F"I think the way the groups are going
OL,14,Fthree points is going to be enough,
OL,15,Fand it's going to come down to the
OL,16,Fgoal difference."
OL,18,FLooking ahead to the final game, Mr
OL,19,FMcNab joked: "It's against Brazil, so
OL,20,Fnot too hard.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUxD@QO]{D@NOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782047474
OL,3,CTartan Army fans still keeping World
OL,4,CCup dream alive despite Morocco defeat
OL,6,F"It's just a case of just keeping it
OL,7,Ftight to the last 15 minutes, and like
OL,8,Fwe've done tonight, just try and go
OL,9,Ffor the last 15 and see what happens."
OL,11,FMartin McCann, 37, from Livingston,
OL,12,Fsaid he was "gutted".
OL,14,F"I wish we went for it a bit more," he
OL,15,Fsaid.
OL,17,F"I'd rather lose by trying to win it,
OL,18,Frather than sitting in, and then you
OL,19,Fconcede anyway.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@fO]tD@MOUtD@TO]vD@AOUvD@cO]yD@
OL,26,AAOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1782047474
OL,3,CTartan Army fans still keeping World
OL,4,CCup dream alive despite Morocco defeat
OL,6,F"But, in reality, a 1-0 defeat keeps
OL,7,Fus in it, so yeah, we go into the next
OL,8,Fgame looking to get enough to get us
OL,9,Fthrough."
OL,11,FAidan Cunningham, 21, from East
OL,12,FKilbride, watched the game in Boston
OL,13,Fcity centre and insisted Scotland were
OL,14,Fthe better team on the night.
OL,16,F"Honestly, when the full-time whistle
OL,17,Fcame I was a little heartbroken," he
OL,18,Fsaid.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@IO]xD@AOUyD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
